            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="aling(right)">
                <placeName>Charleston S. C.</placeName>
                <date>March 3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 5627</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have the honor to enclose you the<lb/> copy of the Resolutions
                unanimously adopted by the Board of<lb/> Trustees at a regular meeting convened this
                day.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Permit me to add, that they embody the<lb/> earnest convictions, and
                sincere wishes, not only of the<lb/> Board of Trustees, but of all the members of
                our<lb/> community, who unite with me in the sincere<lb/> prayer, that the God of
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName> will grant you renewed<lb/> health and strength,
                and length of days, to officiate in<lb/> your sacred functions.</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">With sincere regard</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">I remain very respy</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">Nathaniel Levine</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Secy &amp; <add>?</add> KKBE</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">Extract from the minutes</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">x x x x x x x</p>
            <p>At a regular meeting of the Board of Trustees K. K. B.<lb/> Elohim convened at the
                Vestry room <date>Sunday Adar 23rd<lb/> 5627</date>, the following Resolutions were
                unanimously adopted.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Whereas, the members of this Board have heard with<lb/> great
                satisfaction the very eloquent sermons delivered by<lb/> the <persName>Revd. Isaac
                    Leeser</persName>, in our Synagogue, during the<lb/> past two weeks; and
                although we are sensible that no<lb/> words of praise coming from any quarter can
                increase<lb/> the fame of, or add honor to, that distinguished “light<lb/> in
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName>”, Nevertheless, we feel it due to ourselves<lb/>
                and to the Congregators whom we represpent, to place<lb/> on record our appreciation
                of his efforts, therefore</p>
            <p>Resolved, That the thanks of this Board are hereby<lb/> tendered to the
                    <persName>Revd. Isaac Leeser</persName> for the valuable<lb/> moral and
                religious teachings with which he has<lb/> favored our congregation during his brief
                sojourn<lb/> among us.</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>Resolved, That we hope his health may be<lb/> improved by his visit to the
                    <placeName>South</placeName>, and that<lb/> he may be spared for many years to
                preach and<lb/> teach the words of truth and pure Jewish doctrine.</p>
            <p>Resolved, That a copy of these Resolutions be<lb/> sent to the Revd. Gentleman and
                that they be<lb/> published in the “Occident” &amp; “Jewish Messenger”</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">Nathl. Levine</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Secy &amp; Trease KKBE</p>
